Considered to be the
oldest continuous culture

00:31:34.470 --> 00:31:37.800 align:middle line:10%
on the planet, the
originals of what is now

00:31:37.800 --> 00:31:40.830 align:middle line:10%
called Australia believe
that all creation was

00:31:40.830 --> 00:31:44.760 align:middle line:10%
birthed from what the West
termed as the dreaming.

00:31:44.760 --> 00:31:49.710 align:middle line:10%
The creation of the world,
the origins of knowledge.

00:31:49.710 --> 00:31:51.720 align:middle line:84%
The Indigenous
tribes of Australia

00:31:51.720 --> 00:31:54.030 align:middle line:84%
would use shamanic
ceremonies and miming

00:31:54.030 --> 00:31:56.520 align:middle line:84%
dances to enter
this space in which

00:31:56.520 --> 00:32:00.420 align:middle line:84%
all ancestors and all
information was attainable.

00:32:00.420 --> 00:32:02.580 align:middle line:84%
The Westerners who
attempted to translate

00:32:02.580 --> 00:32:07.000 align:middle line:84%
the meaning of this space
called it dream time.

00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:10.170 align:middle line:10%
Even in the Americas,
accessing the dreaming realm

00:32:10.170 --> 00:32:13.560 align:middle line:10%
was a known phenomena
among the Indigenous.

00:32:13.560 --> 00:32:16.800 align:middle line:10%
>>KUAUHTLI VASQUEZ: Indigenous
people of this continent

00:32:16.800 --> 00:32:23.160 align:middle line:10%
are all from the
same DNA lineage.

00:32:23.160 --> 00:32:28.290 align:middle line:10%
It varies, of course, but
there is a common DNA thread

00:32:28.290 --> 00:32:30.450 align:middle line:10%
of all the Indigenous people.

00:32:30.450 --> 00:32:34.080 align:middle line:10%
Basically, they're all
related, and all of them

00:32:34.080 --> 00:32:38.310 align:middle line:10%
had access to what
we call dream time.

00:32:38.310 --> 00:32:43.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, dream time is
where the humans

00:32:43.080 --> 00:32:46.620 align:middle line:84%
have access to
information that exists

00:32:46.620 --> 00:32:50.070 align:middle line:90%
in interdimensional spheres.

00:32:50.070 --> 00:32:54.870 align:middle line:10%
And the way this was utilized
in pre-American times

00:32:54.870 --> 00:32:57.660 align:middle line:10%
and pre-Hispanic times and
before the colonization

00:32:57.660 --> 00:32:59.340 align:middle line:10%
and the Christianization
and all this

00:32:59.340 --> 00:33:04.240 align:middle line:10%
where they viewed this
as diabolical or useless

00:33:04.240 --> 00:33:06.130 align:middle line:10%
was that they would
find individuals

00:33:06.130 --> 00:33:10.090 align:middle line:10%
that had this ability
to remember their dreams

00:33:10.090 --> 00:33:14.980 align:middle line:10%
and to be aware in their dreams,
and they would group them

00:33:14.980 --> 00:33:18.160 align:middle line:10%
into dreamer societies.

00:33:18.160 --> 00:33:22.840 align:middle line:10%
And they would forge a physical
unity through certain dances,

00:33:22.840 --> 00:33:25.930 align:middle line:10%
through certain songs,
through drumming practices.

00:33:25.930 --> 00:33:28.810 align:middle line:10%
And then they would
go into the dream time

00:33:28.810 --> 00:33:32.980 align:middle line:10%
where they could access
visions of the future, visions

00:33:32.980 --> 00:33:37.240 align:middle line:10%
of the past, visions
of other places.

00:33:37.240 --> 00:33:40.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are some of
the aspects of all of this?

00:33:40.670 --> 00:33:42.290 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLECEK: Oh my goodness.

00:33:42.290 --> 00:33:43.730 align:middle line:90%
So much comes to mind here.

00:33:43.730 --> 00:33:45.770 align:middle line:84%
One thing that
immediately I have to say

00:33:45.770 --> 00:33:50.790 align:middle line:84%
is that these practices,
because they're

00:33:50.790 --> 00:33:52.920 align:middle line:84%
working with unconscious
dimensions of the mind--

00:33:52.920 --> 00:33:56.460 align:middle line:84%
and neuroscience these
days argues very cogently

00:33:56.460 --> 00:34:01.560 align:middle line:84%
that at least 95% of
what we do is actually

00:34:01.560 --> 00:34:04.830 align:middle line:84%
dictated by unconscious
processes, which

00:34:04.830 --> 00:34:07.440 align:middle line:84%
lends tremendous new meaning
to what Christ allegedly

00:34:07.440 --> 00:34:08.489 align:middle line:90%
said on the cross, right?

00:34:08.489 --> 00:34:11.150 align:middle line:84%
Forgive them, father, for
they know not what they do.

00:34:11.150 --> 00:34:13.650 align:middle line:84%
And so what you're doing when
you're working with this stuff

00:34:13.650 --> 00:34:15.567 align:middle line:84%
is you're bringing these
unconscious processes

00:34:15.567 --> 00:34:17.310 align:middle line:90%
into the light of consciousness.

00:34:17.310 --> 00:34:19.469 align:middle line:84%
And in particular,
what's very powerful

00:34:19.469 --> 00:34:22.260 align:middle line:84%
is you are revealing
a host of blind spots.

00:34:22.260 --> 00:34:24.900 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most
insidious of all blind spots

00:34:24.900 --> 00:34:28.020 align:middle line:84%
is actually a type
of discrimination

00:34:28.020 --> 00:34:29.610 align:middle line:84%
that we all suffer
from in the West,

00:34:29.610 --> 00:34:30.790 align:middle line:90%
and we don't even know it.

00:34:30.790 --> 00:34:34.230 align:middle line:84%
It's like what-- they often
attribute it to Mark Twain,

00:34:34.230 --> 00:34:36.550 align:middle line:84%
but Josh Billings
actually said it.

00:34:36.550 --> 00:34:39.100 align:middle line:84%
It's not what you don't know
that gets you in trouble.

00:34:39.100 --> 00:34:42.000 align:middle line:84%
It's what you do know
that just ain't so.

00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:44.489 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the things
you take as axiomatic,

00:34:44.489 --> 00:34:48.183 align:middle line:84%
the things you take as a
given, they're not givens.

00:34:48.183 --> 00:34:49.600 align:middle line:84%
It's called the
myth of the given.

00:34:49.600 --> 00:34:51.090 align:middle line:84%
And so the reason
this is important

00:34:51.090 --> 00:34:56.858 align:middle line:84%
is that Charles Laughlin,
a neuroanthropologist,

00:34:56.858 --> 00:34:58.650 align:middle line:84%
has done a very
interesting set of studies.

00:34:58.650 --> 00:35:00.870 align:middle line:84%
And he estimates that outside
of European cultures--

00:35:00.870 --> 00:35:04.770 align:middle line:84%
there are some 4,000
Indigenous cultures worldwide--

00:35:04.770 --> 00:35:08.700 align:middle line:84%
90% of them are what
are called polyphasic.

00:35:08.700 --> 00:35:11.190 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they
derive their insights

00:35:11.190 --> 00:35:13.590 align:middle line:84%
into mind and reality
from all dimensions

00:35:13.590 --> 00:35:15.420 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness like this.

00:35:15.420 --> 00:35:18.270 align:middle line:90%
In the West, we are monophasic.

00:35:18.270 --> 00:35:19.620 align:middle line:90%
We're wake-centric.

00:35:19.620 --> 00:35:22.410 align:middle line:84%
We derive our insights
from mind and reality

00:35:22.410 --> 00:35:24.150 align:middle line:90%
from the waking state.

00:35:24.150 --> 00:35:29.310 align:middle line:84%
And so therefore, we're
leaving out categorically 2/3

00:35:29.310 --> 00:35:30.400 align:middle line:90%
of reality.

00:35:30.400 --> 00:35:33.240 align:middle line:84%
And this is exactly what
this video revealed.

00:35:33.240 --> 00:35:34.950 align:middle line:84%
So by engaging in
these practices,

00:35:34.950 --> 00:35:36.720 align:middle line:84%
we actually start to
realize, oh my gosh.

00:35:36.720 --> 00:35:40.170 align:middle line:84%
The aperture of my
awareness is so constricted,

00:35:40.170 --> 00:35:43.290 align:middle line:84%
the lens of my mind
is so small, it's

00:35:43.290 --> 00:35:45.930 align:middle line:84%
like the only thing that's
valid and is worth discovering

00:35:45.930 --> 00:35:48.810 align:middle line:84%
is what shines itself
in the light of the day,

00:35:48.810 --> 00:35:50.530 align:middle line:90%
the diurnal activities.

00:35:50.530 --> 00:35:52.530 align:middle line:84%
And what these practices
point out go, you know,

00:35:52.530 --> 00:35:54.270 align:middle line:90%
you're shortchanging yourself.

00:35:54.270 --> 00:35:56.940 align:middle line:84%
You're leaving out
2/3 of reality.

00:35:56.940 --> 00:35:59.850 align:middle line:84%
Look how much you can
experience and learn

00:35:59.850 --> 00:36:01.980 align:middle line:84%
if you maintain lucidity
in the dream state

00:36:01.980 --> 00:36:03.360 align:middle line:90%
and in the sleep state.

00:36:03.360 --> 00:36:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And so again, it just
lends more credibility

00:36:06.120 --> 00:36:11.040 align:middle line:84%
to how we're sitting on top
of this vast, untapped natural

00:36:11.040 --> 00:36:14.160 align:middle line:84%
resource, which is
our unconscious mind.

00:36:14.160 --> 00:36:16.650 align:middle line:84%
And these practices
allow us to bring

00:36:16.650 --> 00:36:18.690 align:middle line:84%
all these unconscious
processes into the light

00:36:18.690 --> 00:36:19.590 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:36:19.590 --> 00:36:22.170 align:middle line:84%
They reveal a host
of blind spots,

00:36:22.170 --> 00:36:24.960 align:middle line:84%
and therefore allow you to see
things that you've actually

00:36:24.960 --> 00:36:26.213 align:middle line:90%
never seen before.

00:36:26.213 --> 00:36:27.630 align:middle line:84%
And so the analogy
I give, George,

00:36:27.630 --> 00:36:30.840 align:middle line:84%
it's like if we were to take
every light in the studio

00:36:30.840 --> 00:36:34.260 align:middle line:84%
and just hit it full
on, super bright,

00:36:34.260 --> 00:36:36.270 align:middle line:84%
and we're hanging out in
this super bright room

00:36:36.270 --> 00:36:38.790 align:middle line:84%
for, I don't know, half an
hour, and then all of the sudden

00:36:38.790 --> 00:36:42.510 align:middle line:84%
there's a total blackout, for
the first couple of minutes,

00:36:42.510 --> 00:36:44.170 align:middle line:90%
you're not going to see a thing.

00:36:44.170 --> 00:36:44.970 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:36:44.970 --> 00:36:49.020 align:middle line:84%
Because your pupils are so
constricted, you can't see.

00:36:49.020 --> 00:36:53.320 align:middle line:84%
But what happens, you
relax, be patient--

00:36:53.320 --> 00:36:54.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And it illuminates.

00:36:54.570 --> 00:36:55.820 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLECEK: Everything dilates.

00:36:55.820 --> 00:36:59.190 align:middle line:84%
That dilation is a dilation
of the aperture of awareness

00:36:59.190 --> 00:37:00.280 align:middle line:90%
itself.

00:37:00.280 --> 00:37:01.380 align:middle line:90%
So as the mind--

00:37:01.380 --> 00:37:05.820 align:middle line:84%
as the eye relaxes, you start
to see things that have always

00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:08.580 align:middle line:84%
been there, but you
hadn't seen them before,

00:37:08.580 --> 00:37:10.650 align:middle line:84%
because your lens, the
aperture of your awareness

00:37:10.650 --> 00:37:12.660 align:middle line:90%
was too constricted.

00:37:12.660 --> 00:37:15.090 align:middle line:84%
And so as we learn to
step into the dark,

00:37:15.090 --> 00:37:18.360 align:middle line:84%
into the nocturnal arena, which
is where we go when nature--

00:37:18.360 --> 00:37:20.970 align:middle line:84%
when we abide by the
natural curfew of the night.

00:37:20.970 --> 00:37:22.900 align:middle line:84%
That's the other thing
that's happening.

00:37:22.900 --> 00:37:24.600 align:middle line:84%
Especially in the
West, light pollution

00:37:24.600 --> 00:37:26.970 align:middle line:90%
is running rampant in this age.

00:37:26.970 --> 00:37:29.820 align:middle line:84%
I think every year, an
annual increase of at least

00:37:29.820 --> 00:37:31.810 align:middle line:90%
6% increase in light over--

00:37:31.810 --> 00:37:32.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Each year?

00:37:32.610 --> 00:37:33.960 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLECEK: Over each year.

00:37:33.960 --> 00:37:37.290 align:middle line:84%
It's having a massive damaging
effect on the ecosystem,

00:37:37.290 --> 00:37:38.680 align:middle line:90%
on our psyches, and whatnot.

00:37:38.680 --> 00:37:41.580 align:middle line:84%
And so as we violate
the natural curfew

00:37:41.580 --> 00:37:43.920 align:middle line:84%
of the night, which
invites us in--

00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:45.640 align:middle line:84%
when it gets dark,
we get inside.

00:37:45.640 --> 00:37:48.060 align:middle line:84%
When we go to bed, we
go inside even further.

00:37:48.060 --> 00:37:49.977 align:middle line:84%
We're missing out on
this profound opportunity

00:37:49.977 --> 00:37:50.777 align:middle line:90%
for growth.

00:37:50.777 --> 00:37:53.070 align:middle line:84%
And even Teilhard de Chardin,
the great anthropologist,

00:37:53.070 --> 00:37:55.530 align:middle line:84%
once said very,
very compellingly,

00:37:55.530 --> 00:37:58.170 align:middle line:84%
evolution hasn't
stopped, connecting it

00:37:58.170 --> 00:37:59.460 align:middle line:90%
to the earlier statement.

00:37:59.460 --> 00:38:01.800 align:middle line:90%
It's only moved indoors.

00:38:01.800 --> 00:38:03.840 align:middle line:84%
And so the evolutionary
trajectory now

00:38:03.840 --> 00:38:04.920 align:middle line:90%
is taking place where?

00:38:04.920 --> 00:38:06.700 align:middle line:90%
At the arena of the mind.

00:38:06.700 --> 00:38:09.690 align:middle line:84%
And so these
practices have so much

00:38:09.690 --> 00:38:13.320 align:middle line:84%
applicability in this
modern age to allow

00:38:13.320 --> 00:38:17.400 align:middle line:84%
us to add a night shift,
to go to night school,

00:38:17.400 --> 00:38:20.660 align:middle line:84%
to bring about this
vast natural resource.

00:38:20.660 --> 00:38:23.640 align:middle line:84%
Tap into it, bring it into
the light of consciousness,

00:38:23.640 --> 00:38:25.620 align:middle line:84%
and fulfill the
Socratic injunction.

00:38:25.620 --> 00:38:28.350 align:middle line:84%
Remember where he
says, know thyself.

00:38:28.350 --> 00:38:30.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So Andrew, where
does this all take us,

00:38:30.810 --> 00:38:32.880 align:middle line:90%
this lucid dream state?

00:38:32.880 --> 00:38:35.460 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLECEK: Ah, great
question, George.

00:38:35.460 --> 00:38:37.120 align:middle line:90%
I think what it does--

00:38:37.120 --> 00:38:39.830 align:middle line:90%
here's the way I look at it.

00:38:39.830 --> 00:38:44.260 align:middle line:84%
It's like walking a labyrinth
into the center of yourself,

00:38:44.260 --> 00:38:48.590 align:middle line:84%
discovering as you take this
nocturnal journey every night

00:38:48.590 --> 00:38:52.270 align:middle line:84%
dimensions of our identity,
dimensions of our being

00:38:52.270 --> 00:38:54.280 align:middle line:84%
that have previously
been restricted.

00:38:54.280 --> 00:38:57.460 align:middle line:84%
So as I mentioned earlier,
it's a kind of consciousness

00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:58.360 align:middle line:90%
hacking, right?

00:38:58.360 --> 00:39:02.470 align:middle line:84%
We're hacking into previously
unconscious domains of mind

00:39:02.470 --> 00:39:05.170 align:middle line:84%
as a way to accelerate
evolution and development.

00:39:05.170 --> 00:39:07.210 align:middle line:84%
But here's where it
gets really interesting,

00:39:07.210 --> 00:39:08.200 align:middle line:90%
because not only does--

00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:09.325 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Here's the kicker.

00:39:09.325 --> 00:39:10.533 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLECEK: Here's the kicker.

00:39:10.533 --> 00:39:12.220 align:middle line:84%
Not only does this
labyrinth take you

00:39:12.220 --> 00:39:13.900 align:middle line:84%
into the center of
yourself, but it also

00:39:13.900 --> 00:39:15.640 align:middle line:90%
doubles as a Mobius strip.

00:39:15.640 --> 00:39:18.160 align:middle line:84%
So I'm bringing two
metaphors into play.

00:39:18.160 --> 00:39:20.628 align:middle line:84%
By going so deeply into
the center of yourself,

00:39:20.628 --> 00:39:21.670 align:middle line:90%
well, guess what happens?

00:39:21.670 --> 00:39:25.180 align:middle line:84%
Like a Mobius strip, you find
yourself coming back out.

00:39:25.180 --> 00:39:29.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why is it
that in our dream state

00:39:29.110 --> 00:39:32.270 align:middle line:84%
we can accomplish things we
can't do when we're awake?

00:39:32.270 --> 00:39:34.450 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLECEK: Oh, it's
because we're actually

00:39:34.450 --> 00:39:38.750 align:middle line:84%
tapping into the more fluid,
dreamlike dimension of reality.

00:39:38.750 --> 00:39:42.130 align:middle line:84%
And so this is a
great topic, George.

00:39:42.130 --> 00:39:44.660 align:middle line:84%
The fundamental nature,
the fabric of reality,

00:39:44.660 --> 00:39:47.080 align:middle line:84%
especially according to
the Tibetan tradition--

00:39:47.080 --> 00:39:50.500 align:middle line:84%
the term is emptiness-- it's a
challenging term to understand.

00:39:50.500 --> 00:39:54.370 align:middle line:84%
But emptiness really translates
as openness, as malleability,

00:39:54.370 --> 00:39:57.370 align:middle line:84%
as flexibility, as
interdependence.

00:39:57.370 --> 00:40:01.570 align:middle line:84%
And so by exploring these
dimensions, you not only

00:40:01.570 --> 00:40:04.660 align:middle line:84%
open to yourself and tap
into these natural resources,

00:40:04.660 --> 00:40:07.960 align:middle line:84%
but George, you find that
you are deeply, inextricably

00:40:07.960 --> 00:40:09.430 align:middle line:84%
connected to every
other sentient

00:40:09.430 --> 00:40:11.920 align:middle line:84%
being on this planet,
because your story is

00:40:11.920 --> 00:40:12.940 align:middle line:90%
different than mine.

00:40:12.940 --> 00:40:15.070 align:middle line:90%
We don't live the same lives.

00:40:15.070 --> 00:40:17.740 align:middle line:84%
But the nature of our
being is the same.

00:40:17.740 --> 00:40:18.700 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But it works.

00:40:18.700 --> 00:40:19.652 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLECEK: It works.

00:40:19.652 --> 00:40:20.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I've tried it a lot.

00:40:20.860 --> 00:40:21.550 align:middle line:90%
It works.

00:40:21.550 --> 00:40:22.350 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLECEK: Exactly.

00:40:22.350 --> 00:40:24.970 align:middle line:84%
And so by
understanding yourself,

00:40:24.970 --> 00:40:26.920 align:middle line:84%
know thyself, when
you understand

00:40:26.920 --> 00:40:28.780 align:middle line:84%
your heart and mind
so profoundly, well,

00:40:28.780 --> 00:40:30.170 align:middle line:90%
guess what happens?

00:40:30.170 --> 00:40:31.720 align:middle line:84%
You understand the
hearts and minds

00:40:31.720 --> 00:40:33.650 align:middle line:90%
of all beings on this planet.

00:40:33.650 --> 00:40:36.400 align:middle line:10%
And so therefore,
the fruition of this

00:40:36.400 --> 00:40:39.940 align:middle line:10%
is tremendous compassion,
kindness, tolerance, empathy,

00:40:39.940 --> 00:40:42.070 align:middle line:10%
openness towards
others, because you

00:40:42.070 --> 00:40:45.610 align:middle line:10%
realize in the most
immediate, first-person way

00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:48.970 align:middle line:10%
that we share the
same bed of mind.

00:40:48.970 --> 00:40:52.120 align:middle line:84%
Every night, we drop
into the same bed

00:40:52.120 --> 00:40:55.090 align:middle line:84%
of mind, the same
fundamental matrix of mind.

00:40:55.090 --> 00:40:57.730 align:middle line:10%
And it's only when we
come up out of that state

00:40:57.730 --> 00:40:59.800 align:middle line:10%
with a type of
amnesia, non-lucidly,

00:40:59.800 --> 00:41:03.040 align:middle line:10%
that we forget the universality
and the commonality

00:41:03.040 --> 00:41:05.410 align:middle line:10%
of the human condition,
that fundamentally we

00:41:05.410 --> 00:41:09.740 align:middle line:10%
are, as the Dalai Lama says
so beautifully, fundamentally,

00:41:09.740 --> 00:41:10.540 align:middle line:10%
we're all the same.

00:41:10.540 --> 00:41:12.237 align:middle line:90%
We all want to be happy.

00:41:12.237 --> 00:41:13.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's the bottom line.

00:41:13.570 --> 00:41:15.320 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLECEK: We all want
to avoid suffering.

00:41:15.320 --> 00:41:17.590 align:middle line:84%
And so this is a beautiful
place to come full circle,

00:41:17.590 --> 00:41:19.480 align:middle line:84%
because these
teachings, again, it

00:41:19.480 --> 00:41:22.750 align:middle line:84%
can seem so esoteric
and so otherworldly.

00:41:22.750 --> 00:41:25.720 align:middle line:84%
They have tremendous
applicability

00:41:25.720 --> 00:41:29.932 align:middle line:84%
to benefiting ourselves,
others, and the planet itself.

00:41:29.932 --> 00:41:32.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Andrew, thanks for
being on "Beyond Belief."

00:41:32.140 --> 00:41:33.340 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLECEK: George, it's
been such a delight.

00:41:33.340 --> 00:41:34.070 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for having me.

00:41:34.070 --> 00:41:34.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Thank you.

00:41:34.870 --> 00:41:35.710 align:middle line:90%
Lucid dreaming.

00:41:35.710 --> 00:41:38.770 align:middle line:10%
When you realize that you
are dreaming in a dream,

00:41:38.770 --> 00:41:41.110 align:middle line:10%
you can do incredible things.

00:41:41.110 --> 00:41:42.160 align:middle line:10%
Try it.

00:41:42.160 --> 00:41:43.210 align:middle line:10%
I'm George Noory.

00:41:43.210 --> 00:41:45.670 align:middle line:84%
Thanks for watching
"Beyond Belief."

00:41:45.670 --> 00:41:49.920 align:middle line:90%
